                  </hi>. I am assistant to Mr. Luxmore, of St. Martin'slane, pawnbroker—this silver watch and gold chain were pawned by the pri<lb></lb>soner on 25th of February, in the name of "Henry Bedford '—I have the duplicate—they were pawned for 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and I think in the early part of the afternoon.</p>
